body:
# Create Linear Issue

Create issues via the GraphQL mutation or SDK.

## GraphQL Mutation

```graphql
mutation CreateIssue($input: IssueCreateInput!) {
  issueCreate(input: $input) {
    success
    issue {
      id
      identifier
      title
      url
      state {
        name
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Variables:

```json
{
  "input": {
    "teamId": "uuid-of-team",
    "title": "Bug: login fails on Safari",
    "description": "## Steps\n1. Open Safari\n2. Navigate to /login\n\n## Expected\nRedirect to dashboard\n\n## Actual\n500 error page",
    "priority": 2,
    "assigneeId": "uuid-of-user",
    "labelIds": ["uuid-of-label"],
    "projectId": "uuid-of-project",
    "stateId": "uuid-of-state",
    "estimate": 3,
    "dueDate": "2026-05-01"
  }
}
```

## SDK Usage

```typescript
import { LinearClient } from "@linear/sdk";

const client = new LinearClient({ apiKey: process.env.LINEAR_API_KEY });

// Find the target team
const teams = await client.teams();
const team = teams.nodes.find(t => t.key === "ENG");
if (!team) throw new Error("Team ENG not found");

// Create the issue
const result = await client.createIssue({
  teamId: team.id,
  title: "Bug: login fails on Safari",
  description: "Steps to reproduce...\n\nExpected: redirect\nActual: 500 error",
  priority: 2,
});

if (result.success) {
  const issue = await result.issue;
  console.log(`Created: ${issue.identifier} — ${issue.url}`);
} else {
  console.error("Failed to create issue");
}
```

## Create with Labels

```typescript
// Find label IDs first
const labels = await client.issueLabels();
const bugLabel = labels.nodes.find(l => l.name === "bug");

const result = await client.createIssue({
  teamId: team.id,
  title: "Fix broken API endpoint",
  labelIds: bugLabel ? [bugLabel.id] : [],
  priority: 1,
});
```

## Create Sub-Issue

```typescript
const result = await client.createIssue({
  teamId: team.id,
  title: "Sub-task: write unit tests",
  parentId: "uuid-of-parent-issue",
});
```

## Create from cURL

```bash
curl -X POST https://api.linear.app/graphql \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: $LINEAR_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "query": "mutation { issueCreate(input: { teamId: \"TEAM_UUID\", title: \"New issue from CLI\" }) { success issue { identifier url } } }"
  }'
```

## Required vs Optional Fields

| Field | Required | Type | Notes |
|-------|----------|------|-------|
| `teamId` | Yes | UUID | Team the issue belongs to |
| `title` | Yes | string | Issue title |
| `description` | No | string | Markdown body |
| `priority` | No | int | 0=none, 1=urgent, 2=high, 3=medium, 4=low |
| `assigneeId` | No | UUID | User to assign |
| `stateId` | No | UUID | Workflow state (defaults to team's default) |
| `labelIds` | No | UUID[] | Labels to apply |
| `projectId` | No | UUID | Associate with a project |
| `cycleId` | No | UUID | Add to a cycle/sprint |
| `estimate` | No | number | Story points or hours |
| `dueDate` | No | string | YYYY-MM-DD format |
| `parentId` | No | UUID | Parent issue for sub-issues |

## Notes

- Omitting `stateId` places the issue in the team's default workflow state (usually Backlog or Triage)
- The `description` field supports full Markdown including images, code blocks, and task lists
- The response's `issue.identifier` gives the human-readable key like `ENG-42`
- Changes within 3 minutes of creation don't appear in Linear's activity feed
